nucleus, the globus pallidus.  Removal of a portion of the lentiform in this manner will reveal the continuation of the corona radiata as the internal capsule. 
The internal capsule consists of projection fibres running medial to the lentiform nucleus. Anteriorly, it lies between the lentiform and the head of the caudate nucleus, forming the anterior limb of the internal capsule. Posteriorly, the internal capsule lies between the lentiform and the thalamus forming the posterior limb of the internal capsule.  The inflection point between the anterior and posterior limbs of the internal capsule is the genu. Identify these structures in the accompanying figure.
